<li>Submit portfolio of current work, including at least 3 pieces.</li>
</ul>
</p>
                                                </td>
                                            </tr>
                                    </tbody>
                                </table>
                        </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row money-and-testimonials-section">
                <div class="col">
                    <div id="howMuchMoney">
                        <h3>How much money is on offer?</h3>
                        <p>
                            The amount of money available through scholarships can vary. Remember that a scholarship will only cover some of your tuition fees. You will still have to fund your remaining tuition fees and your accommodation, insurance, visa and other living costs in full. For more information, see our <a href="/en/fees">fees and finance</a> page.
                        </p>
                    </div>


                        <div id="applicationProcess">
                            <h3>What is the process of applying for a scholarship?</h3>
                            <p>You can only apply for a scholarship if you have also submitted an application to one of our courses. To apply for a scholarship at INTO London, you will need to fill out the <a href="https://www.intostudy.com/Downloads/Application-forms/UK/INTO-scholarship-application-form.pdf">scholarship application form</a>, and send it - along with copies of the documents listed below - to <a href="mailto:intolondon@intoglobal.com" title="intolondon@intoglobal.com">intolondon@intoglobal.com</a>.</p>
<p>The documents you’ll need to provide are:</p>
<ul>
<li>Your offer letter</li>
<li>Your latest academic transcript</li>
<li>Evidence of your English language proficiency</li>
<li>A one page personal statement</li>
</ul>
<p>Your application will be reviewed by a scholarship panel, and if successful you will be notified via the email address provided on your application form.</p>

                        </div>
                </div>



